# Verification Strategy

> The harness refuses to call any work "done" until verification has run and
> returned a PASS verdict. Hard gate; not a recommendation.

## The 7-layer defense-in-depth stack
| # | Layer | Catches |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Static (lint, types, format, secrets, LSP) | Surface errors |
| 2 | Unit + property | Functional correctness of units |
| 3 | Integration | Cross-component contracts |
| 4 | End-to-end user-flow | "App appears to work but breaks for users" |
| 5 | Behavioural fingerprinting | Regressions binary pass/fail misses |
| 6 | Mutation testing | Tests-that-don't-test |
| 7 | Trace audit | Agent lying about what it did |

## The 4-tier judge stack (when LLM judgement needed)
| Tier | What | When |
|---|---|---|
| J0 | Deterministic graders (exit codes, schemas) | Whenever ground truth exists |
| J1 | Distilled small judge per rubric (Phi-3-mini, Llama-3.1-8B) | Production: every action |
| J2 | OS structured judge (Prometheus 2) | Batch / nightly |
| J3 | Frontier spot-check (Opus, GPT-frontier) | 1% sampling, quarterly calibration |
| J4 | Pairwise + self-consistency voting | Version comparisons |

**Non-negotiable: the model that generated the artifact must not grade it.**

## The 4 anti-gaming primitives
| | Rule | Why |
|---|---|---|
| AG-1 | Snapshot tests before run; restore before grading | Stops "I modified tests to pass" |
| AG-2 | Compare claimed actions vs actual diffs | Catches lying about results |
| AG-3 | Deliberately break code; verify tests FAIL | Closes "no real tests" tautology |
| AG-4 | E2E asserts on UI-text + server-state both | Eliminates #1 false-pass mode |

## Sandbox tiers
- S0 (~s): headless container, no rendering — default for most runs.
- S1 (~10s): container + display + input simulation — native GUI without WebView.
- S2 (~30s): microVM with kernel isolation — malicious-persona, untrusted code.
- S3 (~min): real VM, per-OS runners — top-level mission validation.

## Personas
novice / expert / distracted / malicious / mobile / edge-case. Same scenario as
"novice" vs "expert" should produce DIFFERENT verdicts — if not, verification
isn't testing what users do.

## Recording → replay → calibration
Every session recorded by default. Recordings drive replay (regression),
mutation testing, and the calibration dataset for judge retraining.
